Here's a simple HTML and CSS code to create a basic website with the theme "Enjoy the Journey of Life." This example uses GitHub Pages for deployment, but you can use any platform you prefer.

### HTML (index.html)

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Enjoy the Journey of Life</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Enjoy the Journey of Life</h1>
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#home">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
                <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <section id="home">
        <h2>Welcome</h2>
        <p>Life is a journey filled with amazing experiences. Embrace every moment and enjoy the ride.</p>
        <img src="journey.jpg" alt="Journey">
    </section>

    <section id="about">
        <h2>About This Site</h2>
        <p>This site is dedicated to appreciating the beauty and joy in life's journey. We believe that every step, no matter how small, contributes to the grand adventure that is life.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="contact">
        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>Feel free to reach out to us at <a href="mailto:info@example.com">info@example.com</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 Enjoy the Journey of Life</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

### CSS (styles.css)

```css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    background-color: #f9f9f9;
}

header {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: white;
    padding: 15px 0;
    text-align: center;
}

nav ul {
    list-style-type: none;
    padding: 0;
}

nav ul li {
    display: inline;
    margin: 0 10px;
}

nav ul li a {
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
}

section {
    padding: 20px;
    margin: 20px;
    background-color: white;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

h1, h2 {
    color: #333;
}

p {
    color: #555;
}

img {
    max-width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    margin: 20px auto;
}

footer {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 10px 0;
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: white;
    position: fixed;
    width: 100%;
    bottom: 0;
}
```

### Steps to Deploy Using GitHub Pages

1. **Create a GitHub Repository**:
   - Go to [GitHub](https://github.com) and create a new repository named `username.github.io`, replacing `username` with your GitHub username.

2. **Clone the Repository**:
   - Clone the repository to your local machine using Git.
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/username/username.github.io
   ```

3. **Add Your Files**:
   - Copy the `index.html` and `styles.css` files into your cloned repository.

4. **Commit and Push**:
   - Add, commit, and push your changes to GitHub.
   ```bash
   git add .
   git commit -m "Initial commit"
   git push origin main
   ```

5. **View Your Site**:
   - Your site will be live at `https://username.github.io`.

You can customize the content, images, and styles as per your preference to make the site more personal and appealing.
